#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
cyberos — operator CLI for .cyberos-memory/ stores.

Single umbrella binary wrapping the existing runtime/tools/ Python scripts +
adding the missing operator verbs. Per Aspect 1.1 of the Layer-1 improvement
catalog.

Usage:
    cyberos status                    # 4-operator-question dashboard (Aspect 2.1)
    cyberos verify                    # delegates to cyberos_validate.py
    cyberos doctor [args...]          # delegates to cyberos_doctor.py
    cyberos export [args...]          # delegates to cyberos_export.py
    cyberos search <query>            # search via cyberos_index.py
    cyberos add <type> <slug>         # interactive memory creation (M1, not yet implemented)
    cyberos show [filter]             # list memories (not yet implemented)
    cyberos prune                     # staleness / contradiction (not yet implemented)
    cyberos stats                     # bucket / class / authority counts
    cyberos voice [path]              # voice linter (Aspect 7.2, not yet implemented)
    cyberos hooks [on|off]            # PreToolUse hook toggle (Aspect 5.1, not yet implemented)
    cyberos panic                     # emergency stop (Aspect 13.10, not yet implemented)
    cyberos help [cmd]                # detailed help per subcommand

Run from anywhere inside a cyberos project. Locates `.cyberos-memory/` by
walking up from CWD per §0.1.

Implemented (today):     status, verify, doctor, export, search, stats, help, version
Not yet implemented:     add, show, prune, voice, hooks, panic, repl, onboard, sync, conflicts, eval, analytics

Each "not yet implemented" subcommand prints the Aspect number from the
Layer-1 improvement catalog (cyberos-layer1-deep-improvements.md) so you
know which improvement ships it.

Local-only by contract. Reads + writes only the project's `.cyberos-memory/`.
"""
